{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/opioid-dependence/goals-outcome-measures/goals/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"5766349b-04fe-548c-9de5-0ff28c7803b9","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 06370e86-f14e-4d89-be43-3a3774823ea3 --><h2>Goals</h2><!-- end field 06370e86-f14e-4d89-be43-3a3774823ea3 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 53037083-6acd-4283-9553-5984064b6a0b --><!-- begin field 3c088a66-79ea-4df6-b0d0-0584f4390556 --><p>To support primary healthcare professionals to:</p><ul><li>Help a person with opioid dependence to remain healthy.</li><li>Reduce the harm associated with illicit drug misuse.</li><li>Reduce the dangers associated with injecting and sharing equipment (hepatitis A, B, and C; HIV; other blood-borne infections; streptococcal and staphylococcal infections; and deep vein thrombosis).</li><li>Help a person with opioid dependence to achieve a stable life.</li><li>Help a person overcome their dependence.</li><li>Establish the person on maintenance treatment if abstinence is not possible at a sufficient dose to prevent or avoid withdrawal effects, reduce and stop illicit drug misuse, and support change in other areas of life.</li></ul><!-- end field 3c088a66-79ea-4df6-b0d0-0584f4390556 --><!-- end item 53037083-6acd-4283-9553-5984064b6a0b -->","topic":{"id":"ef534296-f504-5d3e-9b47-3c0f08322658","topicId":"1acd30d9-6aea-492b-a570-5fbeb05d49f5","topicName":"Opioid dependence","slug":"opioid-dependence","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2020","chapters":[{"id":"7b9e0e1a-3aea-5219-a001-dfd22a786292","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"a0179729-bb50-55a3-a1dc-ca3cbd473972","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e63e1346-068d-56e6-891b-85878800d361","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-dat